.SS Example 1: A simplified Witchcraft setup
.sp
In Witchcraft, besides the various Gifted classes, characters can be spirits
There are spirit realms to which the mundane can not travel. Therefore we
will use 2 reality levels: Real and Ghost. Since some spirits can become
solid for a limited period of time, we will also use an additional desc for
the Ghost level, called GHOSTDESC. Therefore in the config file we will
have:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.nf
.ft C
reality_level Real 1
reality_level Ghost 2 GHOSTDESC
.ft P
.fi
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
Ghosts can pass through most mundane locks, so the exists should allows the
ghosts to pass:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.nf
.ft C
def_exit_rx 3
.ft P
.fi
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
Note that def_exit_tx isn\(aqt set. Why? Because ghosts see the mundane world
anyway, so a spirit character will have:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.nf
.ft C
@txlevel <player>=!Real Ghost
@rxlevel <player>=Real Ghost
.ft P
.fi
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
Let\(aqs assume 3 players:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.nf
.ft C
John is a Mundane. He won\(aqt see spirits.
John\(aqs Rx: Real
John\(aqs Tx: Real
John\(aqs @desc: This is John.
John\(aqs &GHOSTDESC: (Not important, since it\(aqs never visible)
Johh\(aqs @adesc: %N has looked at you.
John\(aqs @odesc: has looked at John.
.ft P
.fi
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
Jack is a Gifted. He will sense spirits, but is still made from flesh and blood so visible to mundanes:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.nf
.ft C
Jack\(aqs Rx: Real Ghost
Jack\(aqs Tx: Real
Jack\(aqs @desc: This is Jack.
Jack\(aqs &GHOSTDESC: (Not important, since it\(aqs never visible)
Jack\(aqs @adesc: %N has looked at you.
Jack\(aqs @odesc: has looked at Jack.
.ft P
.fi
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
Frank is a ghost. He will see other spirits as well as mundanes, but won\(aqt be visible to mundanes. He can also become visible to everybody:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.nf
.ft C
Frank\(aqs Rx: Real Ghost
 Frank\(aqs Tx: Ghost
